







       The window Menu, sometimes called the system Menu, is used
       to display the list of window actions.  All actions possible
       for a window should be displayed in the window Menu, since
       keyboard-only users interact with the window manager through
       this Menu.

       The window Menu button must be located in the upper-left
       corner of the window.  Double-clicking the window Menu but-
       ton must close the window.  Pressing KKKKWWWWiiiinnnnddddoooowwwwMMMMeeeennnnuuuu must
       activate the window Menu button for the window with the
       focus.  The illustration on this reference page shows a
       posted window Menu.

